node.text:
“So many will never understand how much sacrifice has been made to maintain the freedoms so many take for granted. May God Bless America and Bless be the families of our Fallen for they have paved the way. To our Fallen, you will never be forgotten because they are those of us who will refuse to kneel and continue the fight against the evil powers trying to destroy the best country on earth and our people. We will prevail! 

Today let it be a reminder that courage, honor, bravery is the corner stone of our nation best we can offer and our National cemetery’s are this undaunted sacrifice.

Remember them everyday for the day we will forget them, is they day our nation and our people have succumbed to complete tyranny.”

#usarmy #usaf #usmarines #usnavy #uscg #woundedwarriorproject #heroes #freedom #liberty #memorialday🇺🇸 #memorialdayweekend2021 #memorialday2021 #ronaldreagan 
#memorialday #memorialdayweekend

node.text:
Before you say this is not political intimidation, if you’re marching to someone’s office in uniform with a member of the opposing party, that makes it political. If you’re then doing it and there are cameras documenting, you’re being used as a prop. 

This could have been cleared up by calling, emailing, or sending a gift basket. Not this debacle of a PR stunt using the military in order to send a message.

Now, this does not mean you should harass this unit. It pretty clear from my perspective that they were used regardless of their good intentions.
